CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 20, 1953, page 23, reads: "Local Merchants - Bob West, proprietor of West Auto Body Shop, and his assistant, Wilmer Bass, drew attention to their display by adding this attractive but unidentified young lady."
TitMainTitle: Bob West and Wilmer Bass standing on either side of woman wearing light colored dress, in West Auto Body booth, in Ammon Center for 1953 Pittsburgh Courier Home Service Fair, another version
